<h1>Play It My Way! <span style="text-shadow: 0 0 1em green, 0 0 0.2em blue; ">Beta.</span></h1>
<div style="clear: both;"></div>
<h1>Streaming Edited Movie playback for you or your family.</h1>
<br/>Take back control over what your view in your home! 
<br/>Ever wished you could mute profanities or skip objectionable scenes that distract during movies?  We believe you should have the ability to watch shows "your way" in the privacy of your home, and we're here to help.  We have a database of "tags" of video content, and you can also add personalized tags.
<br/>
<a href="#demo" class="btn btn-info" data-toggle="collapse">How it works</a>
<div id="demo" class="collapse">
  We provide you the ability to edit your movie when you stream it from amazon or youtube, so you can choose which parts you watch.  So we don't actually stream the movies, per se, we just edit them.
  <div id=how_it_works >
    Basically, watch your movie like normal on your computer, our plugin will edit out the parts you don't want, see <a href=/getting_started>Getting Started</a> to install it!
    <br/>
    Plus if you notice something that should be tagged, you can tag it in our system and everybody, including yourself, will benefit!
  </div>
</div>
<br/>
<a href="#cost" class="btn btn-info" data-toggle="collapse">How much does it cost?</a>
<div id="cost" class="collapse">
Play It My Way is currently free while in Beta! For movies, we eventually plan to make it a "$1/filter or subscribe for $5/month", but during Beta, it's free.  The filters are free but the streaming may or may not be depending on your subscriptions and which movies you have previously purchased.  So there are two prices at play here, the cost of renting/streaming the movie to begin with, and then the cost of adding our editing software on top of that.  The latter is currently free :)
<br/>
During beta, the only thing you have to pay for is the streaming cost.
<br/>

Edited youtube's are "community driven" and will always be free, you can even tag your own to add them to our system!
</div>
